tion` - Scientifically optimize a system prompt\n5. `/failure_mode_predict` - Predict where an agent will fail given its configuration\n\n\n6. `/cognitive_alignment_score` - How well does the agent understand user intent?\n\nThis is far more valuable than generic LLM wrappers because it applies specialized cognitive science expertise directly to improving how AI systems think and perform.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Now we're talking. **That's a real moat.**\n\nAgents can't self-diagnose their own cognitive blind spots. They need external expertise—and computational cognitive science is exactly that.\n\n**What you could sell A2A:**\n\n| Endpoint | What It Does | Why Agents Pay |\n|----------|--------------|----------------|\n| `/calibration_audit` | Assess confidence vs accuracy | Agents don't know what they don't know |\n| `/bias_scan` | Detect systematic reasoning biases | Can't see your own blind spots |\n| `/reasoning_trace_analysis` | Analyze chain-of-thought for flaws | External QA on thinking process |\n| `/prompt_optimization` | Scientifically improve system prompts | Better than \"prompt engineering\" guesswork |\n| `/failure_mode_predict` | Predict where agent will break | Prevent failures before deployment |\n| `/cognitive_alignment_check` | Does agent actually understand user intent? | Alignment verification |\n\n**Why this works:**\n- **Expertise moat** — requires real cognitive science knowledge\n- **Can't DIY** — agents can't objectively audit themselves\n- **High value** — miscalibrated agents cost money, cause errors\n- **Recurring** — agents need ongoing calibration as they evolve\n\n**Think of it as:** QA for agent cognition. Therapy for AI reasoning. Cognitive diagnostics as a service.\n\nShould I rebuild the catalog around this? I'd need to understand more about your specific methodologies to design the right endpoints."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-opus-4-5","usage":{"input":10,"output"