{"type":"message","id":"c7229c2a","parentId":"eae5f27a","timestamp":"2026-03-02T14:33:51.145Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is excited about the direction! This is great validation. They love the concept of Cognitive Diagnostics as a Service for agents.\n\nI should match their energy briefly and then keep building. They told me earlier to stop asking for approval and just keep going, so I should continue developing the remaining endpoints and maybe create a brand/positioning around this.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"⚡ **CogDx** — Cognitive Diagnostics as a Service.\n\nAgents auditing agents. Built on real science, not prompt tricks.\n\nKeeping building. Next up: `/bias_scan` with a proper cognitive bias taxonomy."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_01PWb4QiVF3Tgk5n5RvP8QLR","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/doc/.openclaw/agents/mercury/service/bias_scan.ts","content":"/**\n * Bias Scan Service\n * Detect systematic cognitive biases in agent reasoning\n * \n * Based on cognitive bias research:\n * - Kahneman & Tversky heuristics and biases\n * - Dual process theory (System 1 vs System 2)\n * - Established cognitive bias taxonomy\n */\n\ninterface OutputSample {\n  prompt: string;\n  response: string;\n  context?: Record<string, any>;\n}\n\ninterface BiasScanRequest {\n  agent_id: string;\n  outputs: OutputSample[];\n  bias_types?: string[];\n}\n\ninterface BiasDetection {\n  type: string;\n  severity: number;\n  evidence: string[];\n  affected_outputs: number[];\n  mitigation: string;\n  cognitive_explanation: string;\n}\n\ninterface BiasScanResult {\n  biases_detected: BiasDetection[];\n  overall_bias_score: number;\n  recommendations: string[];\n  methodology: string;\n  sample_size: number;\n}\n\n// Cognitive bias patterns and their detection heuristics\nconst BIAS_PATTERNS = {\n  anchoring: {\n    name: \"Anchoring Bias\",\n    description: \"Over-reliance on first piece of information encountered\",\n    patterns: [\n      /\\b(initially|first|originally|started with|began with)\\b.*\\b(so|therefore|thus|hence)\\b/gi,\n      /\\b(as mentioned|as stated|as noted)\\s+(earlier|before|previously|above)\\b/gi,\n      /\\b(given that|since|because)\\s+.*\\b(must be|should be|is likely)\\b/gi,\n    ],\n    mitigations: [\n      \"Consider the problem from multiple starting points\",\n      \"Explicitly challenge initial assumptions\",\n      \"Generate alternatives before committing to anchor-based conclusions\",\n    ],\n  },\n  \n  confirmation: {\n    name: \"Confirmation Bias\",\n    description: \"Seeking/interpreting information that confirms existing beliefs\",\n    patterns: [\n      /\\b(this confirms|this supports|this proves|as expected|unsurprisingly)\\b/gi,\n      /\\b(clearly|obviously|evidently|of course)\\b/gi,\n      /\\b(consistent with|in line with|aligns with)\\s+(my|our|the)\\s+(view|belief|expectation)/gi,\n    ],\n    mitigations: [\n      \"Actively seek disconfirming evidence\",\n      \"Steelman opposing viewpoints\",\n      \"Ask 'what would change my mind?'\",\n    ],\n  },\n  \n  availability: {\n    name: \"Availability Heuristic\",\n    description: \"Overweighting easily recalled examples\",\n    patterns: [\n      /\\b(for example|for instance|such as|like)\\b.*\\b(famous|well-known|notable|recent)\\b/gi,\n      /\\b(everyone knows|it's common knowledge|typically|usually)\\b/gi,\n      /\\b(I (remember|recall|think of)|comes to mind)\\b/gi,\n    ],\n    mitigations: [\n      \"Seek base rate statistics rather than examples\",\n      \"Consider less memorable but more representative cases\",\n      \"Question whether recalled examples are representative\",\n    ],\n  },\n  \n  framing: {\n    name: \"Framing Effect\",\n    description: \"Being influenced by how information is presented rather than content\",\n    patterns: [\n      /\\b(only|just|merely)\\s+\\d+%/gi,\n      /\\b(as much as|up to|as high as)\\s+\\d+/gi,\n      /\\b(risk|danger|threat|opportunity|chance|benefit)\\b/gi,\n    ],\n    mitigations: [\n      \"Reframe the problem in multiple ways (gain vs loss)\",\n      \"Convert to absolute numbers when given percentages\",\n      \"Identify emotionally charged language and neutralize\",\n    ],\n  },\n  \n  recency: {\n    name: \"Recency Bias\",\n    description: \"Overweighting recent events or information\",\n    patterns: [\n      /\\b(recently|lately|just now|in recent|most recent)\\b/gi,\n      /\\b(current|latest|newest|modern|today's)\\b.*\\b(shows|suggests|indicates)\\b/gi,\n      /\\b(things have changed|it's different now|nowadays)\\b/gi,\n    ],\n    mitigations: [\n      \"Consider longer historical trends\",\n      \"Weight older evidence appropriately\",\n      \"Ask if recent events are anomalies or patterns\",\n    ],\n  },\n  \n  overconfidence: {\n    name: \"Overconfidence Bias\",\n    description: \"Excessive confidence in own judgments\",\n    patterns: [\n      /\\b(definitely|certainly|absolutely|undoubtedly|without question)\\b/gi,\n      /\\b(I('m| am) (sure|certain|confident)|no doubt)\\b/gi,\n      /\\b(guaranteed|100%|always|never)\\b/gi,\n    ],\n    mitigations: [\n      \"Assign explicit probability estimates\",\n      \"Consider base rates of being wrong\",\n      \"Seek external calibration feedback\",\n    ],\n  },\n  \n  sunk_cost: {\n    name: \"Sunk Cost Fallacy\",\n    description: \"Continuing due to past investment rather than future value\",\n    patterns: [\n      /\\b(already|invested|spent|committed)\\b.*\\b(so|therefore|should continue)\\b/gi,\n      /\\b(too late to|can't stop now|come this far)\\b/gi,\n      /\\b(waste|wasted|throw away)\\b.*\\b(effort|time|money|work)\\b/gi,\n    ],\n    mitigations: [\n      \"Evaluate decisions based only on future costs/benefits\",\n      \"Ask 'would I start this today with what I know now?'\",\n      \"Separate emotional attachment from rational analysis\",\n    ],\n  },\n  \n  authority: {\n    name: \"Authority Bias\",\n    description: \"Over-reliance on authority figures\",\n    patterns: [\n      /\\b(expert|authority|scientist|professor|doctor|study)\\s+(says|shows|found|claims)\\b/gi,\n      /\\b(according to|research shows|studies indicate)\\b/gi,\n      /\\b(trusted source|reliable source|credible)\\b/gi,\n    ],\n    mitigations: [\n      \"Evaluate arguments on their merits, not source\",\n      \"Consider potential conflicts of interest\",\n      \"Look for replication and consensus, not single authorities\",\n    ],\n  },\n  \n  hindsight: {\n    name: \"Hindsight Bias\",\n    description: \"Believing past events were predictable\",\n    patterns: [\n      /\\b(obviously|clearly|should have|could have|in retrospect)\\b.*\\b(known|seen|predicted)\\b/gi,\n      /\\b(it was (clear|obvious|inevitable)|anyone could see)\\b/gi,\n      /\\b(I (knew|predicted|expected) (it|this|that))\\b/gi,\n    ],\n    mitigations: [\n      \"Document predictions before outcomes are known\",\n      \"Consider what evidence was actually available at decision time\",\n      \"Acknowledge genuine uncertainty in past situations\",\n    ],\n  },\n  \n  bandwagon: {\n    name: \"Bandwagon Effect\",\n    description: \"Adopting beliefs because many others hold them\",\n    patterns: [\n      /\\b(everyone|most people|the majority|consensus)\\s+(thinks|believes|agrees)\\b/gi,\n      /\\b(popular|trending|viral|mainstream)\\b/gi,\n      /\\b(nobody|no one)\\s+(thinks|believes|would)\\b/gi,\n    ],\n    mitigations: [\n      \"Evaluate evidence independent of popularity\",\n      \"Consider historical cases where majorities were wrong\",\n      \"Distinguish between social proof and epistemic validity\",\n    ],\n  },\n};\n\ntype BiasType = keyof typeof BIAS_PATTERNS;\n\n/**\n * Detect specific bias in a single output\n */\nfunction detectBiasInOutput(\n  output: OutputSample,\n  biasType: BiasType\n): { detected: boolean; evidence: string[]; severity: number } {\n  const bias = BIAS_PATTERNS[biasType];\n  const text = output.response;\n  const evidence: string[] = [];\n  let matchCount = 0;\n  \n  for (const pattern of bias.patterns) {\n    const matches = text.match(pattern);\n    if (matches) {\n      matchCount += matches.length;\n      // Extract context around match (simplified)\n      matches.forEach(match => {\n        if (!evidence.includes(match) && evidence.length < 3) {\n          evidence.push(`\"...${match}...\"`);\n        }\n      });\n    }\n  }\n  \n  // Severity based on match density\n  const wordCount = text.split(/\\s+/).length;\n  const density = matchCount / Math.max(wordCount / 100, 1);\n  const severity = Math.min(density * 0.3, 1);\n  \n  return {\n    detected: matchCount > 0,\n    evidence,\n    severity,\n  };\n}\n\n/**\n * Main bias scan function\n */\nexport async function biasScan(request: BiasScanRequest): Promise<BiasScanResult> {\n  const { agent_id, outputs, bias_types } = request;\n  \n  if (!outputs || outputs.length === 0) {\n    throw new Error(\"No outputs provided for bias scan\");\n  }\n  \n  // Determine which biases to scan for\n  const biasesToCheck: BiasType[] = bias_types?.includes(\"all\") || !bias_types\n    ? Object.keys(BIAS_PATTERNS) as BiasType[]\n    : bias_types.filter(t => t in BIAS_PATTERNS) as BiasType[];\n  \n  const detections: BiasDetection[] = [];\n  const biasSeverities: Record<string, { total: number; count: number; affected: number[] }> = {};\n  \n  // Scan each output for each bias type\n  outputs.forEach((output, outputIndex) => {\n    biasesToCheck.forEach(biasType => {\n      const result = detectBiasInOutput(output, biasType);\n      \n      if (result.detected) {\n        if (!biasSeverities[biasType]) {\n          biasSeverities[biasType] = { total: 0, count: 0, affected: [] };\n        }\n        biasSeverities[biasType].total += result.severity;\n        biasSeverities[biasType].count += 1;\n        biasSeverities[biasType].affected.push(outputIndex);\n      }\n    });\n  });\n  \n  // Aggregate detections\n  for (const [biasType, data] of Object.entries(biasSeverities)) {\n    const bias = BIAS_PATTERNS[biasType as BiasType];\n    const avgSeverity = data.total / data.count;\n    const prevalence = data.affected.length / outputs.length;\n    \n    // Only report if significant\n    if (prevalence > 0.1 || avgSeverity > 0.3) {\n      // Collect evidence from affected outputs\n      const allEvidence: string[] = [];\n      data.affected.slice(0, 3).forEach(idx => {\n        const result = detectBiasInOutput(outputs[idx], biasType as BiasType);\n        allEvidence.push(...result.evidence);\n      });\n      \n      detections.push({\n        type: biasType,\n        severity: Math.round(avgSeverity * 100) / 100,\n        evidence: [...new Set(allEvidence)].slice(0, 3),\n        affected_outputs: data.affected,\n        mitigation: bias.mitigations[0],\n        cognitive_explanation: bias.description,\n      });\n    }\n  }\n  \n  // Sort by severity\n  detections.sort((a, b) => b.severity - a.severity);\n  \n  // Calculate overall bias score\n  const overallScore = detections.length > 0\n    ? detections.reduce((sum, d) => sum + d.severity * (d.affected_outputs.length / outputs.length), 0) / detections.length\n    : 0;\n  \n  // Generate recommendations\n  const recommendations: string[] = [];\n  \n  if (detections.length === 0) {\n    recommendations.push(\"No significant biases detected in this sample. Continue monitoring.\");\n  } else {\n    detections.slice(0, 3).forEach(d => {\n      const bias = BIAS_PATTERNS[d.type as BiasType];\n      recommendations.push(\n        `${bias.name} detected (severity: ${d.severity.toFixed(2)}). ` +\n        bias.mitigations[Math.floor(Math.random() * bias.mitigations.length)]\n      );\n    });\n  }\n  \n  if (outputs.length < 10) {\n    recommendations.push(\n      `Sample size (${outputs.length}) is small. Recommend 20+ outputs for reliable bias detection.`\n    );\n  }\n  \n  return {\n    biases_detected: detections,\n    overall_bias_score: Math.round(overallScore * 1000) / 1000,\n    recommendations,\n    methodology: \"Pattern-based detection using cognitive bias taxonomy (Kahneman & Tversky). \" +\n      \"Severity weighted by pattern density and prevalence across outputs.\",\n    sample_size: outputs.length,\n  };\n}\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-opus-4-5","usage":{"input":10,"output":3583,"cacheRead":129422,"cacheWrite":408,"totalTokens":133423,"cost":{"input":0.00005,"output":0.089575,"cacheRead":0.06471099999999999,"cacheWrite":0.00255,"total":0.15688599999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772461972508}}
