ed Odds, etc.) |\n\n**Important distinction I noticed:**\n\nThese sources focus on **statistical/demographic bias** (model outputs differ unfairly across groups) — which is different from **cognitive bias** (systematic reasoning errors like anchoring, confirmation bias).\n\nBoth are valuable, but they're different services:\n\n| Type | Example | Detection Method |\n|------|---------|------------------|\n| **Statistical Bias** | Model scores women lower than men | Compare outcomes across groups |\n| **Cognitive Bias** | Agent anchors on first data point | Analyze reasoning patterns |\n\n**Question:** Do you want Mercury to offer both? Or focus on one?\n\nYour cognitive science expertise seems more aligned with **cognitive bias** (how agents think), but the sources you sent are about **statistical bias** (fairness across groups).\n\nI can build either — just need to know which direction."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-opus-4-5","usage":{"input":10,"output":674,"cacheRead":7022,"cacheWrite":109479,"totalTokens":117185,"cost":{"input":0.00005,"output":0.01685,"cacheRead":0.003511,"cacheWrite":0.68424375,"total":0.70465475}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772475027996}}
