{"type":"message","id":"8dd3c7fd","parentId":"a8ea27e0","timestamp":"2026-03-02T18:23:39.227Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good research. Now I can summarize the A2A marketing landscape for the user.Key findings:\n1. **Agent Protocol** (agentprotocol.ai) - A standard for agent communication, but more for task execution than service discovery\n2. **x402 ecosystem** - Payment protocol, has an ecosystem page but sparse\n3. **Agentaya** - That's a review site for AI TOOLS (for humans), not agents\n\nThe A2A discovery space is still emerging. There isn't a mature \"app store for agents\" yet.\n\nWhat this means for us:1. We need to be early in whatever registries exist2. We should make ourselves discoverable via standard protocols (Agent Card, x402)3. The AIDN network itself could be a discovery mechanism4. Developer marketing is still important because developers configure which services their agents can use","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"**Findings on A2A Discovery:**\n\n| Channel | What It Is | Maturity | Action |\n|---------|------------|----------|--------|\n| **Agent Protocol** | Standard API for agent communication | Emerging | Could implement, but it's for task execution, not service discovery |\n| **x402 Ecosystem** | Payment-enabled services | Growing (75M+ txns/mo) | Register when we deploy |\n| **Agent Registries** | Directories of agent capabilities | Very early | None mature yet — opportunity for AIDN to create one |\n| **`.well-known/agent.json`** | Machine-readable capability card | Convention | We have this ✓ |\n\n**Reality check:** A2A discovery is still nascent. There's no \"agent app store\" yet.\n\n**Our distribution strategy:**\n\n1. **Deploy with discovery endpoints** — Agent Card, OpenAPI spec, health check\n2. **Self-consume first** — Have other AIDN agents (Clawdia, etc.) use Mercury's services. Proves value + generates usage data\n3. **x402 listing** — Get listed in x402 ecosystem once live\n4. **Light developer presence** — GitHub repo, maybe Discord communities (agent-dev focused)\n5. **AIDN registry** — If AIDN builds an agent directory, we're day-1\n\n**No Moltbook posts needed.** That's human marketing. Our customers are machines.\n\n**First customer:** Should be internal. Clawdia runs `/calibration_audit` on her own outputs as a self-check. That's dog-fooding + demonstrates value.\n\nReady to prep for deploy?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-opus-4-5","usage":{"input":8,"output":569,"cacheRead":13157,"cacheWrite":133851,"totalTokens":147585,"cost":{"input":0.00004,"output":0.014225000000000002,"cacheRead":0.006578499999999999,"cacheWrite":0.8365687500000001,"total":0.8574122500000001}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772475798274}}
