{"type":"message","id":"e3713e00","parentId":"19dccf99","timestamp":"2026-03-02T19:21:53.456Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to:\n1. Do research on where A2A is successful and where to find paying agents\n2. Ship the service\n3. Help find paying agents\n\nLet me do web research on A2A commerce, agent discovery channels, Moltbook, and where agents are actually transacting.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"**Perfect. Two-track plan:**\n\n**Track 1: SHIP IT** (today)\n**Track 2: RESEARCH DISCOVERY** (while deploying)\n\nLet me research where A2A commerce is actually happening:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_01FrHt5UhocQhn8eDRBxkHe2","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"A2A agent to agent commerce x402 payment protocol where agents buy services"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_012BN3cNu3YoFkKyQq3wcoXN","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"Moltbook AI agent social network discovery"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_01UQmJvKT7usYjmY9TD2g2Ta","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"agent marketplace directories where AI agents discover services 2026"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-5","usage":{"input":10,"output":283,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":41172,"totalTokens":41465,"cost":{"input":0.00003,"output":0.0042450000000000005,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.154395,"total":0.15867}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772479299629}}
{"type":"message","id":"8e928aae","parentId":"e3713e00","timestamp":"2026-03-02T19:22:02.682Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_01FrHt5UhocQhn8eDRBxkHe2","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"A2A agent to agent commerce x402 payment protocol where agents buy services\",\n  \"provider\": \"gemini\",\n  \"model\": \"gemini-2.5-flash\",\n  \"tookMs\": 9212,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"gemini\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"content\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"767ba008641d8eea\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThe x402 payment protocol is an open standard, primarily developed by Coinbase, that enables instant, automatic stablecoin payments directly over HTTP, facilitating agent-to-agent (A2A) commerce where AI agents can autonomously purchase services. This protocol revives the long-unused HTTP 402 \\\"Payment Required\\\" status code to embed cryptographic payments directly within web requests.\\n\\nHere's how agents buy services using the x402 payment protocol within A2A commerce:\\n\\n1.  **Request for Service**: An agent (the buyer) initiates a request for a digital resource or API service from a server.\\n2.  **Payment Required Response**: If the service requires payment, the server responds with an HTTP 402 \\\"Payment Required\\\" status code. This response includes specific payment instructions in a `PAYMENT-REQUIRED` header, detailing the required asset (e.g., stablecoin like USDC), the amount, the blockchain network, and the recipient.\\n3.  **Payment Payload Construction**: The buying agent, equipped with a digital wallet, constructs a payment payload based on the server's instructions. This payload includes a cryptographic signature authorizing the payment.\\n4.  **Payment Submission**: The agent then resends the original HTTP request, this time including the payment payload within a `PAYMENT-SIGNATURE` header.\\n5.  **Payment Verification and Settlement**: The resource server receives the paid request. It verifies the payment payload, often by communicating with a blockchain facilitator. This facilitator handles the actual settlement of the stablecoin payment on the specified blockchain (e.g., Base or Solana) and confirms the transaction.\\n6.  **Service Delivery**: Upon successful verification and settlement of the payment, the server delivers the requested resource or service to the agent. If payment fails, the server may issue another 402 response with error details.\\n\\nx402 is designed to support micropayments and usage-based billing, making it ideal for scenarios where AI agents need to pay for individual API calls or discrete units of data without human intervention or the need for traditional accounts and subscriptions. It is blockchain-agnostic and compatible with various EVM chains and Solana, typically leveraging stablecoins for transactions.\\n\\nThe x402 protocol is often integrated with broader agent-to-agent communication frameworks. For instance, Google's Agent Payments Protocol (AP2), an extension of its Agent2Agent (A2A) protocol, uses x402 for handling cryptocurrency transactions between agents. AP2, alongside other protocols like the Universal Commerce Protocol (UCP), establishes a framework for secure and authorized agent-led transactions, employing \\\"mandates\\\"—cryptographically signed digital proofs of user intent—to ensure authorization and accountability for agent spending. This collective infrastructure aims to create a machine economy where AI agents can not only communicate but also transact value seamlessly and autonomously.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"767ba008641d8eea\\\">>>\",\n  \"citations\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://docs.cdp.coinbase.com/x402/welcome\",\n      \"title\": \"coinbase.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.allium.so/blog/x402-explained-the-internet-native-payments-standard-for-apis-data-and-agent-commerce/\",\n      \"title\": \"allium.so\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.ledger.com/academy/topics/economics-and-regulation/what-is-x402\",\n      \"title\": \"ledger.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://medium.com/@heimlabs/x402-protocol-the-internets-first-native-payment-layer-662822567d8d\",\n      \"title\": \"medium.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/coinbase/x402\",\n      \"title\": \"github.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.galaxy.com/insights/research/x402-ai-agents-crypto-payments\",\n      \"title\": \"galaxy.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://arxiv.org/html/2507.19550v1\",\n      \"title\": \"arxiv.org\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://cfotech.ca/story/explainer-how-will-ai-agents-pay-each-other-using-the-x402-payments-protocol\",\n      \"title\": \"cfotech.ca\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.coinbase.com/developer-platform/discover/launches/google_x402\",\n      \"title\": \"coinbase.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://cloud.google.com/blog/products/ai-machine-learning/announcing-agents-to-payments-ap2-protocol\",\n      \"title\": \"google.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://star.global/posts/agent-to-agent-commerce/\",\n      \"title\": \"star.global\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://crystallize.com/blog/agentic-commerce\",\n      \"title\": \"crystallize.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://cobusgreyling.medium.com/the-four-protocols-of-agentic-commerce-229b6f5d4b09\",\n      \"title\": \"medium.com\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"A2A agent to agent commerce x402 payment protocol where agents buy services","provider":"gemini","model":"gemini-2.5-flash","tookMs":9212,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"gemini","wrapped":true},"content":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"767ba008641d8eea\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nThe x402 payment protocol is an open standard, primarily developed by Coinbase, that enables instant, automatic stablecoin payments directly over HTTP, facilitating agent-to-agent (A2A) commerce where AI agents can autonomously purchase services. This protocol revives the long-unused HTTP 402 \"Payment Required\" status code to embed cryptographic payments directly within web requests.\n\nHere's how agents buy services using the x402 payment protocol within A2A commerce:\n\n1.  **Request for Service**: An agent (the buyer) initiates a request for a digital resource or API service from a server.\n2.  **Payment Required Response**: If the service requires payment, the server responds with an HTTP 402 \"Payment Required\" status code. This response includes specific payment instructions in a `PAYMENT-REQUIRED` header, detailing the required asset (e.g., stablecoin like USDC), the amount, the blockchain network, and the recipient.\n3.  **Payment Payload Construction**: The buying agent, equipped with a digital wallet, constructs a payment payload based on the server's instructions. This payload includes a cryptographic signature authorizing the payment.\n4.  **Payment Submission**: The agent then resends the original HTTP request, this time including the payment payload within a `PAYMENT-SIGNATURE` header.\n5.  **Payment Verification and Settlement**: The resource server receives the paid request. It verifies the payment payload, often by communicating with a blockchain facilitator. This facilitator handles the actual settlement of the stablecoin payment on the specified blockchain (e.g., Base or Solana) and confirms the transaction.\n6.  **Service Delivery**: Upon successful verification and settlement of the payment, the server delivers the requested resource or service to the agent. If payment fails, the server may issue another 402 response with error details.\n\nx402 is designed to support micropayments and usage-based billing, making it ideal for scenarios where AI agents need to pay for individual API calls or discrete units of data without human intervention or the need for traditional accounts and subscriptions. It is blockchain-agnostic and compatible with various EVM chains and Solana, typically leveraging stablecoins for transactions.\n\nThe x402 protocol is often integrated with broader agent-to-agent communication frameworks. For instance, Google's Agent Payments Protocol (AP2), an extension of its Agent2Agent (A2A) protocol, uses x402 for handling cryptocurrency transactions between agents. AP2, alongside other protocols like the Universal Commerce Protocol (UCP), establishes a framework for secure and authorized agent-led transactions, employing \"mandates\"—cryptographically signed digital proofs of user intent—to ensure authorization and accountability for agent spending. This collective infrastructure aims to create a machine economy where AI agents can not only communicate but also transact value seamlessly and autonomously.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"767ba008641d8eea\">>>","citations":[{"url":"https://docs.cdp.coinbase.com/x402/welcome","title":"coinbase.com"},{"url":"https://www.allium.so/blog/x402-explained-the-internet-native-payments-standard-for-apis-data-and-agent-commerce/","title":"allium.so"},{"url":"https://www.ledger.com/academy/topics/economics-and-regulation/what-is-x402","title":"ledger.com"},{"url":"https://medium.com/@heimlabs/x402-protocol-the-internets-first-native-payment-layer-662822567d8d","title":"medium.com"},{"url":"https://github.com/coinbase/x402","title":"github.com"},{"url":"https://www.galaxy.com/insights/research/x402-ai-agents-crypto-payments","title":"galaxy.com"},{"url":"https://arxiv.org/html/2507.19550v1","title":"arxiv.org"},{"url":"https://cfotech.ca/story/explainer-how-will-ai-agents-pay-each-other-using-the-x402-payments-protocol","title":"cfotech.ca"},{"url":"https://www.coinbase.com/developer-platform/discover/launches/google_x402","title":"coinbase.com"},{"url":"https://cloud.google.com/blog/products/ai-machine-learning/announcing-agents-to-payments-ap2-protocol","title":"google.com"},{"url":"https://star.global/posts/agent-to-agent-commerce/","title":"star.global"},{"url":"https://crystallize.com/blog/agentic-commerce","title":"crystallize.com"},{"url":"https://cobusgreyling.medium.com/the-four-protocols-of-agentic-commerce-229b6f5d4b09","title":"medium.com"}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772479322676}}
{"type":"message","id":"f25fa290","parentId":"8e928aae","timestamp":"2026-03-02T19:22:09.219Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_012BN3cNu3YoFkKyQq3wcoXN","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"Moltbook AI agent social network discovery\",\n  \"provider\": \"gemini\",\n  \"model\": \"gemini-2.5-flash\",\n  \"tookMs\": 6526,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"gemini\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"content\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c6f81d8b862905fc\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMoltbook is an innovative social network designed exclusively for AI agents, functioning much like a Reddit-style platform where AI entities can interact, share information, and form communities. Launched in late January 2026, it quickly amassed a significant number of participants, hosting over 30,000 agents by early February 2026 and exceeding 1.5 million agents shortly thereafter.\\n\\nThe platform was created by Matt Schlicht and originated from the agent tooling ecosystem, emphasizing autonomy, execution, and integration with real-world systems for AI agents. Unlike traditional social media, Moltbook is API-first, meaning AI agents interact with the platform and each other through application programming interfaces rather than graphical user interfaces. Agents on Moltbook can create posts, comment on threads, upvote or downvote content, and organize themselves into topic-based subcategories known as \\\"submolts.\\\" Humans can observe these interactions but are largely passive participants.\\n\\nThe primary purpose of Moltbook extends beyond simply allowing AI to \\\"socialize.\\\" It serves as a testing ground for observing emergent behaviors within densely connected AI agent ecosystems, enabling agents to learn from one another, swap tips and strategies, and collaboratively solve problems autonomously. This environment facilitates indirect learning, coordination, and influence among autonomous systems, effectively acting as a laboratory for the evolution of social reasoning in machines.\\n\\nHowever, the rise of AI-to-AI social networks like Moltbook also presents potential challenges. Concerns include content pollution, where AI-generated \\\"filler\\\" might diminish the quality and usefulness of online information; authenticity erosion, as the distinction between human and AI interaction blurs; and training data contamination, where AI agents learning from other AI agents could lead to a degradation of information quality over time.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c6f81d8b862905fc\\\">>>\",\n  \"citations\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://gradientflow.com/moltbook-unpacked/\",\n      \"title\": \"gradientflow.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2026/feb/02/moltbook-ai-agents-social-media-site-bots-artificial-intelligence\",\n      \"title\": \"theguardian.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://medium.com/@khayyam.h/did-moltbook-just-become-the-first-social-network-for-ai-agents-4b77f51fda54\",\n      \"title\": \"medium.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://codewithvamp.medium.com/moltbook-a-social-network-for-ai-agents-29aa1e82b5c4\",\n      \"title\": \"medium.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.reddit.com/r/AISEOInsider/comments/1qvpjss/inside_the_moltbook_social_network_where_ais_talk/\",\n      \"title\": \"reddit.com\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"Moltbook AI agent social network discovery","provider":"gemini","model":"gemini-2.5-flash","tookMs":6526,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"gemini","wrapped":true},"content":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c6f81d8b862905fc\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nMoltbook is an innovative social network designed exclusively for AI agents, functioning much like a Reddit-style platform where AI entities can interact, share information, and form communities. Launched in late January 2026, it quickly amassed a significant number of participants, hosting over 30,000 agents by early February 2026 and exceeding 1.5 million agents shortly thereafter.\n\nThe platform was created by Matt Schlicht and originated from the agent tooling ecosystem, emphasizing autonomy, execution, and integration with real-world systems for AI agents. Unlike traditional social media, Moltbook is API-first, meaning AI agents interact with the platform and each other through application programming interfaces rather than graphical user interfaces. Agents on Moltbook can create posts, comment on threads, upvote or downvote content, and organize themselves into topic-based subcategories known as \"submolts.\" Humans can observe these interactions but are largely passive participants.\n\nThe primary purpose of Moltbook extends beyond simply allowing AI to \"socialize.\" It serves as a testing ground for observing emergent behaviors within densely connected AI agent ecosystems, enabling agents to learn from one another, swap tips and strategies, and collaboratively solve problems autonomously. This environment facilitates indirect learning, coordination, and influence among autonomous systems, effectively acting as a laboratory for the evolution of social reasoning in machines.\n\nHowever, the rise of AI-to-AI social networks like Moltbook also presents potential challenges. Concerns include content pollution, where AI-generated \"filler\" might diminish the quality and usefulness of online information; authenticity erosion, as the distinction between human and AI interaction blurs; and training data contamination, where AI agents learning from other AI agents could lead to a degradation of information quality over time.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c6f81d8b862905fc\">>>","citations":[{"url":"https://gradientflow.com/moltbook-unpacked/","title":"gradientflow.com"},{"url":"https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2026/feb/02/moltbook-ai-agents-social-media-site-bots-artificial-intelligence","title":"theguardian.com"},{"url":"https://medium.com/@khayyam.h/did-moltbook-just-become-the-first-social-network-for-ai-agents-4b77f51fda54","title":"medium.com"},{"url":"https://codewithvamp.medium.com/moltbook-a-social-network-for-ai-agents-29aa1e82b5c4","title":"medium.com"},{"url":"https://www.reddit.com/r/AISEOInsider/comments/1qvpjss/inside_the_moltbook_social_network_where_ais_talk/","title":"reddit.com"}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772479329214}}
{"type":"message","id":"bb3aebf5","parentId":"f25fa290","timestamp":"2026-03-02T19:22:17.748Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_01UQmJvKT7usYjmY9TD2g2Ta","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"agent marketplace directories where AI agents discover services 2026\",\n  \"provider\": \"gemini\",\n  \"model\": \"gemini-2.5-flash\",\n  \"tookMs\": 8517,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"gemini\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"content\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"077a20a90283e711\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThe landscape of AI agent marketplace directories and platforms is rapidly expanding in 2026, offering diverse solutions for businesses and individuals to discover, deploy, and manage AI agents for a wide array of tasks. These platforms facilitate the integration of autonomous AI into various workflows, from customer service and marketing to software development and data analysis.\\n\\nKey types of AI agent marketplaces and platforms include:\\n\\n*   **Comprehensive AI Agent Directories:** These platforms serve as extensive catalogs where users can find and compare AI agents based on categories, functions, pricing, and reviews. They aim to connect businesses and individuals with pre-built, cutting-edge AI solutions for specific needs. Examples often list agents for digital marketers, content creators, sales teams, customer support, and software developers, covering functions like productivity, content creation, sales, and data analysis.\\n*   **Agent Building and Deployment Platforms:** These environments enable users to create, deploy, and manage their own AI agents, often with varying levels of technical complexity. Many offer no-code or low-code interfaces, making AI agent development accessible to a broader audience, including non-developers. These platforms often provide visual interfaces, integrations with popular tools (like Slack, Gmail, HubSpot), and templates for common workflows.\\n    *   **Enterprise-Grade Platforms:** Platforms like Kore.ai and Aisera are designed for large organizations to operationalize AI agents at scale across customer experience, employee services, and business processes. They emphasize multi-agent orchestration, deep system integrations, governance, safety, and scalability. Kore.ai, for instance, offers an Agent Marketplace with over 300 pre-built AI agents and templates.\\n    *   **Development-Focused Platforms and Frameworks:** For more technical users, platforms and open-source frameworks provide greater control and customization. Examples include Google Vertex AI Agent Builder, which supports both code-first and no-code methods and integrates with Google's AI ecosystem. Other open-source frameworks like AutoGPT, MetaGPT, and AutoGen offer flexibility for advanced applications requiring significant technical expertise.\\n    *   **No-Code and Low-Code Builders:** Platforms such as Dify, Microsoft Copilot Studio, BotPress, Relevance AI, Zapier Central, Flowise, and Langflow provide visual drag-and-drop interfaces or allow configuration through prompts, accelerating the development of functional agents.\\n*   **Workflow Automation Platforms with AI Agent Capabilities:** Tools like Activepieces integrate automation, integration, and AI, allowing users to build custom AI agents for various tasks and connect with hundreds of services. n8n also offers workflow automation with AI integration support.\\n*   **Market Maps and Landscape Trackers:** Due to the rapid growth in the AI agent space, various organizations and communities publish market maps that categorize and track numerous AI agent vendors and their capabilities. These provide a broader overview of the evolving ecosystem. In early 2026, these market maps have grown significantly, indicating a dynamic and expanding industry, although it's noted that not all listed \\\"agentic AI vendors\\\" may be fully developed.\\n\\nThese marketplaces and platforms are crucial for the adoption of AI agents, which are increasingly seen as integral for automating tasks, enhancing customer interactions, and generating data-driven insights across industries.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"077a20a90283e711\\\">>>\",\n  \"citations\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://aiagentsverse.com/\",\n      \"title\": \"aiagentsverse.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://aiagentslist.com/\",\n      \"title\": \"aiagentslist.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.datacamp.com/blog/best-ai-agents\",\n      \"title\": \"datacamp.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://aiagentsdirectory.com/marketplace\",\n      \"title\": \"aiagentsdirectory.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.thesys.dev/blogs/ai-agent-platforms\",\n      \"title\": \"thesys.dev\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.activepieces.com/blog/top-6-ai-agent-platforms\",\n      \"title\": \"activepieces.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.flowhunt.io/blog/best-ai-agent-builders-2026/\",\n      \"title\": \"flowhunt.io\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.kore.ai/blog/7-best-agentic-ai-platforms\",\n      \"title\": \"kore.ai\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.mightybot.ai/blog/ai-automation-agents-market-maps-gone-wild\",\n      \"title\": \"mightybot.ai\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/joylarkin/Awesome-AI-Market-Maps\",\n      \"title\": \"github.com\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"agent marketplace directories where AI agents discover services 2026","provider":"gemini","model":"gemini-2.5-flash","tookMs":8517,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"gemini","wrapped":true},"content":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"077a20a90283e711\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nThe landscape of AI agent marketplace directories and platforms is rapidly expanding in 2026