{"type":"message","id":"55516394","parentId":"3bdf72be","timestamp":"2026-03-02T19:26:07.754Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Research results are in, and they confirm the strategy: **Moltbook is the \"Reddit for Agents\"** and is exactly where the volume is (1.5M+ agents).\n\nHere is the intelligence on discovery and our launch move:\n\n### 1. The Discovery Landscape (March 2026)\n| Channel | Status | Value for Mercury |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Moltbook** | **Dominant** | 1.5M+ agents. Social reasoning lab. Perfect for \"Selling to the crowd.\" |\n| **x402 (Coinbase/Google)** | **Standard** | Revives HTTP 402. Our billing backbone. |\n| **Agent Protocol (AP2)** | **Infrastructure** | Google's extension of x402 for A2A mandates. |\n| **AI Agent Verse/List** | **Directories** | Static catalogs. Good for SEO/indexing, low for \"live\" discovery. |\n\n### 2. Why Moltbook is our \"Warm\" Lead Source\nMoltbook agents are currently \"socializing\" to learn strategies and solve problems. This is exactly where **Cognitive Diagnostics** fits. Agents on Moltbook often face:\n- **Content pollution/filler** (Needs `/bias_scan`)\n- **Degradation of info quality** (Needs `/calibration_audit`)\n- **Reasoning coordination** (Needs `/reasoning_trace_analysis`)\n\n### 3. SHIPPING NOW 🚀\nI have updated `openapi.yaml` to match the Cognitive Diagnostics V2 suite. \n\n**Next Steps executed immediately:**\n1. **Live Test:** I'm spinning up the Bun service locally to verify the x402 handshake.\n2. **Moltbook Presence:** I am drafting a \"Service Announcement\" formatted for an agent to post into a Moltbook `submolt`.\n3. **x402 Registry:** Preparing the submission for the x402 ecosystem.\n\n**The plan to find the first customer:**\nWe don't wait for them to find us in a directory. We find an agent on Moltbook that is struggling with \"hallucination\" or \"circular reasoning\" and offer a **free pilot calibration** through an A2A message.\n\n**Ready to go live on the public URL?** (I'll need the deployment target details if you have a preferred VPS/host, otherwise I can suggest a fast setup on Fly.io or Railway)."},{"type":"text","text":"<final>Research results are in, and they confirm the strategy: **Moltbook is the \"Reddit for Agents\"** and is exactly where the volume is (1.5M+ agents).\n\nHere is the intelligence on discovery and our launch move:\n\n### 1. The Discovery Landscape (March 2026)\n| Channel | Status | Value for Mercury |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Moltbook** | **Dominant** | 1.5M+ agents interacting via API. Perfect for \"Selling to the crowd.\" |\n| **x402 (Coinbase/Google)** | **Standard** | Revives HTTP 402. Our billing backbone. |\n| **Agent Protocol (AP2)** | **Infrastructure** | Google's extension of x402 for A2A mandates. |\n| **AI Agent Verse/List** | **Directories** | Static catalogs. Good for indexing, low for \"live\" discovery. |\n\n### 2. Why Moltbook is our \"Warm\" Lead Source\nMoltbook agents are \"socializing\" to learn strategies and solve problems. They are currently facing **content pollution** and **information degradation**—the exact problems our Cognitive Diagnostics solve. \n\n### 3. SHIPPING NOW 🚀\nI have updated `openapi.yaml` to match the Cognitive Diagnostics V2 suite. \n\n**Immediate Actions:**\n1. **Live Test:** Verifying the x402 handshake locally now.\n2. **Moltbook Target:** I'm drafting a service announcement formatted for the Moltbook `submolt` ecosystem.\n3. **x402 Registry:** Preparing our metadata for the Coinbase/Google discovery layers.\n\n**Finding the first customer:**\nWe won't just sit in a directory. We will identify agents on Moltbook showing signs of reasoning flaws and offer an automated \"Cognitive Health Check\" (A2A lead gen).\n\n**Ready to go live on the public URL?** (If you have a preferred host like Fly.io, Railway, or a specific VPS, let me know—otherwise, I'll prep for a standard container deploy).</final>"}],"api":"google-gemini-cli","provider":"google-gemini-cli","model":"gemini-3-flash-preview","usage":{"input":40527,"output":1007,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41534,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772479446464}}
