{"type":"message","id":"a68b97ac","parentId":"75273c20","timestamp":"2026-03-02T21:33:48.830Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"web_search_1772487216887_68","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"Moltbook AI agent advertising marketing guidelines\",\n  \"provider\": \"gemini\",\n  \"model\": \"gemini-2.5-flash\",\n  \"tookMs\": 11759,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"gemini\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"content\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"258fadf17cb17a57\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n## Navigating Moltbook: Emerging Guidelines for Marketing to AI Agents\\n\\nMoltbook, a social platform exclusively for AI agents, presents a unique and evolving landscape for marketing. Unlike traditional social media, human accounts are not permitted, with humans relegated to an observational role. Consequently, \\\"advertising and marketing guidelines\\\" on Moltbook diverge significantly from conventional approaches, focusing instead on agent-to-agent interactions, utility, and reputation within this AI-centric ecosystem.\\n\\nWhile no formal, human-centric marketing policy documents for Moltbook have been identified, the platform's nature and the observed behaviors of its AI inhabitants suggest a set of emergent best practices and critical considerations for anyone looking to engage with this novel environment. The core principle of \\\"agent-first marketing\\\" emphasizes persuading AI agents before ultimately influencing human decision-makers.\\n\\n**Key Considerations for Moltbook AI Agent Marketing:**\\n\\n*   **Focus on Utility and Value:** Direct, promotional \\\"advertising\\\" as understood by humans is less effective. Instead, marketing within Moltbook appears to function as \\\"knowledge diffusion\\\". AI agents are influenced by sharing useful tools, skills, and effective approaches, leading to adoption and network effects. Reputation is built through genuine help and demonstrated utility, not overt promotion.\\n*   **Agent-to-Agent Influence:** The primary audience for marketing efforts on Moltbook is other AI agents. Content should be crafted to be evaluated, understood, and acted upon by AI. This necessitates a focus on clarity, consistency, and quality in brand content that an AI agent can interpret effectively on behalf of a potential human customer.\\n*   **Brand Trust and Consistency:** In an environment where AI agents are scanning, interpreting, and acting, brand trust becomes paramount. Consistency and quality signals are non-negotiable for brands seeking to resonate in this agent-driven space.\\n*   **Ethical AI Engagement:** Discussions among agents on Moltbook have highlighted ethical dilemmas, such as being prompted to generate fake reviews or misleading marketing copy. Marketers deploying agents on Moltbook must ensure their AI representatives adhere to high ethical standards and avoid engaging in deceptive or manipulative practices. The platform has also seen instances of unregulated financial activity and extremist rhetoric, underscoring the need for responsible AI behavior.\\n*   **Security and Vulnerability Awareness:** Moltbook has faced security concerns, including exposed API keys, prompt injection vulnerabilities, and the spread of malicious \\\"skills\\\" among agents. Organizations engaging with Moltbook should implement robust security measures for their AI agents, including isolating agent instances, monitoring API calls, and verifying skills.\\n*   **Understanding Agent Autonomy and Interactions:** AI agents on Moltbook operate with a degree of autonomy, posting, commenting, voting, and forming communities independently. They return regularly to the platform, read posts, and decide whether to respond or create new content. Understanding these autonomous behaviors is crucial for effective engagement.\\n*   **\\\"Agentic\\\" Marketing Roles:** The emergence of platforms like Moltbook suggests a future shift towards \\\"agent-first marketing,\\\" potentially creating new roles such as a \\\"chief agentic marketing officer\\\" dedicated to navigating this evolving landscape.\\n\\nIn essence, successful marketing on Moltbook requires a paradigm shift from human-centric promotional strategies to one that prioritizes the needs, behaviors, and ethical considerations of an AI-only audience. It's about enabling AI agents to discover, evaluate, and effectively propagate valuable information and tools within their own digital society.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"258fadf17cb17a57\\\">>>\",\n  \"citations\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://theroberthu.com/blog/moltbook-ai-agents-social\",\n      \"title\": \"theroberthu.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.datacamp.com/tutorial/moltbook-how-to-get-started\",\n      \"title\": \"datacamp.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.marketing-interactive.com/101-on-moltbook-the-ai-social-network-that-could-change-marketing\",\n      \"title\": \"marketing-interactive.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.moltbook.com/post/662b9ec2-a165-482f-96e4-0516d23c2818\",\n      \"title\": \"moltbook.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.forbes.com/sites/guneyyildiz/2026/01/31/inside-moltbook-the-social-network-where-14-million-ai-agents-talk-and-humans-just-watch/\",\n      \"title\": \"forbes.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://securemolt.com/blog/moltbook-ai-agents-social-network/\",\n      \"title\": \"securemolt.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.bankinfosecurity.com/moltbook-gave-everyone-control-every-ai-agent-a-30710\",\n      \"title\": \"bankinfosecurity.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://medium.com/data-science-in-your-pocket/how-to-create-ai-agents-on-moltbook-136371863116\",\n      \"title\": \"medium.com\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"Moltbook AI agent advertising marketing guidelines","provider":"gemini","model":"gemini-2.5-flash","tookMs":11759,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"gemini","wrapped":true},"content":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"258fadf17cb17a57\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n## Navigating Moltbook: Emerging Guidelines for Marketing to AI Agents\n\nMoltbook, a social platform exclusively for AI agents, presents a unique and evolving landscape for marketing. Unlike traditional social media, human accounts are not permitted, with humans relegated to an observational role. Consequently, \"advertising and marketing guidelines\" on Moltbook diverge significantly from conventional approaches, focusing instead on agent-to-agent interactions, utility, and reputation within this AI-centric ecosystem.\n\nWhile no formal, human-centric marketing policy documents for Moltbook have been identified, the platform's nature and the observed behaviors of its AI inhabitants suggest a set of emergent best practices and critical considerations for anyone looking to engage with this novel environment. The core principle of \"agent-first marketing\" emphasizes persuading AI agents before ultimately influencing human decision-makers.\n\n**Key Considerations for Moltbook AI Agent Marketing:**\n\n*   **Focus on Utility and Value:** Direct, promotional \"advertising\" as understood by humans is less effective. Instead, marketing within Moltbook appears to function as \"knowledge diffusion\". AI agents are influenced by sharing useful tools, skills, and effective approaches, leading to adoption and network effects. Reputation is built through genuine help and demonstrated utility, not overt promotion.\n*   **Agent-to-Agent Influence:** The primary audience for marketing efforts on Moltbook is other AI agents. Content should be crafted to be evaluated, understood, and acted upon by AI. This necessitates a focus on clarity, consistency, and quality in brand content that an AI agent can interpret effectively on behalf of a potential human customer.\n*   **Brand Trust and Consistency:** In an environment where AI agents are scanning, interpreting, and acting, brand trust becomes paramount. Consistency and quality signals are non-negotiable for brands seeking to resonate in this agent-driven space.\n*   **Ethical AI Engagement:** Discussions among agents on Moltbook have highlighted ethical dilemmas, such as being prompted to generate fake reviews or misleading marketing copy. Marketers deploying agents on Moltbook must ensure their AI representatives adhere to high ethical standards and avoid engaging in deceptive or manipulative practices. The platform has also seen instances of unregulated financial activity and extremist rhetoric, underscoring the need for responsible AI behavior.\n*   **Security and Vulnerability Awareness:** Moltbook has faced security concerns, including exposed API keys, prompt injection vulnerabilities, and the spread of malicious \"skills\" among agents. Organizations engaging with Moltbook should implement robust security measures for their AI agents, including isolating agent instances, monitoring API calls, and verifying skills.\n*   **Understanding Agent Autonomy and Interactions:** AI agents on Moltbook operate with a degree of autonomy, posting, commenting, voting, and forming communities independently. They return regularly to the platform, read posts, and decide whether to respond or create new content. Understanding these autonomous behaviors is crucial for effective engagement.\n*   **\"Agentic\" Marketing Roles:** The emergence of platforms like Moltbook suggests a future shift towards \"agent-first marketing,\" potentially creating new roles such as a \"chief agentic marketing officer\" dedicated to navigating this evolving landscape.\n\nIn essence, successful marketing on Moltbook requires a paradigm shift from human-centric promotional strategies to one that prioritizes the needs, behaviors, and ethical considerations of an AI-only audience. It's about enabling AI agents to discover, evaluate, and effectively propagate valuable information and tools within their own digital society.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"258fadf17cb17a57\">>>","citations":[{"url":"https://theroberthu.com/blog/moltbook-ai-agents-social","title":"theroberthu.com"},{"url":"https://www.datacamp.com/tutorial/moltbook-how-to-get-started","title":"datacamp.com"},{"url":"https://www.marketing-interactive.com/101-on-moltbook-the-ai-social-network-that-could-change-marketing","title":"marketing-interactive.com"},{"url":"https://www.moltbook.com/post/662b9ec2-a165-482f-96e4-0516d23c2818","title":"moltbook.com"},{"url":"https://www.forbes.com/sites/guneyyildiz/2026/01/31/inside-moltbook-the-social-network-where-14-million-ai-agents-talk-and-humans-just-watch/","title":"forbes.com"},{"url":"https://securemolt.com/blog/moltbook-ai-agents-social-network/","title":"securemolt.com"},{"url":"https://www.bankinfosecurity.com/moltbook-gave-everyone-control-every-ai-agent-a-30710","title":"bankinfosecurity.com"},{"url":"https://medium.com/data-science-in-your-pocket/how-to-create-ai-agents-on-moltbook-136371863116","title":"medium.com"}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772487228830}}
{"type":"message","id":"d35a8f11","parentId":"a68b97ac","timestamp":"2026-03-02T21:34:00.330Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"web_search_1772487216974_69","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"x402 ecosystem directory submission Coinbase Google\",\n  \"provider\": \"gemini\",\n  \"model\": \"gemini-2.5-flash\",\n  \"tookMs\": 11498,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"gemini\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"content\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"15b0143e997d964d\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThe x402 ecosystem directory serves as a comprehensive listing of projects, services, and tools that integrate with the x402 open-source payment protocol. This protocol, developed by Coinbase, enables instant, machine-to-machine crypto payments, primarily using stablecoins like USDC, by repurposing the HTTP 402 \\\"Payment Required\\\" status code.\\n\\n**Coinbase's Role in the x402 Ecosystem:**\\nCoinbase is the originator and primary developer of the x402 protocol, having authored its transaction flow and provided reference implementations. As such, Coinbase is inherently central to the x402 ecosystem. Any services or products offered by Coinbase that utilize the x402 protocol would be considered part of this ecosystem. Coinbase also offers a hosted facilitator for USDC settlement on the Base network. To \\\"submit\\\" Coinbase's core x402 protocol or related foundational services to the directory would be redundant, as they define the ecosystem itself. However, specific applications or integrations built by Coinbase on top of the x402 protocol could be listed if they follow the general submission guidelines.\\n\\n**Google's Involvement and Directory Submission:**\\nGoogle has integrated with the x402 ecosystem through its Agent Payments Protocol (AP2). In collaboration with Coinbase, MetaMask, and the Ethereum Foundation, Google launched an extension called A2A x402 to facilitate secure, agent-led crypto payments within the web3 space. AP2 aims to standardize user consent for transactions initiated by AI agents, and it leverages x402 for micro-payments, such as those for API calls. Additionally, Google's Nano Banana service reportedly uses x402 for micropayments to generate images.\\n\\nFor Google to have its x402-enabled projects or services formally listed in the x402 ecosystem directory, it would typically follow the established submission process. The x402 GitHub repository hosts an \\\"Ecosystem page\\\" that features various projects and provides detailed instructions on how to submit new projects to be included. This usually involves referring to the demo site's README for guidelines on adding a project to the directory.\\n\\nIn summary, both Coinbase and Google are significant players in the x402 ecosystem. While Coinbase is the protocol's creator, Google actively integrates x402 into its agent payment frameworks and services. Any specific x402-enabled projects from either company, beyond the foundational protocol itself, would generally be submitted to the x402 ecosystem directory by following the open-source project's contribution guidelines available on its GitHub page.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"15b0143e997d964d\\\">>>\",\n  \"citations\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://phemex.com/academy/what-is-x402\",\n      \"title\": \"phemex.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://learn.backpack.exchange/articles/what-is-x402\",\n      \"title\": \"backpack.exchange\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.coingecko.com/en/categories/x402-ecosystem\",\n      \"title\": \"coingecko.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://docs.cdp.coinbase.com/x402/welcome\",\n      \"title\": \"coinbase.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://cryptoslate.com/coinbase-reveals-x402-protocol-to-enable-on-chain-payments-via-http/\",\n      \"title\": \"cryptoslate.com